  <preparation>Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat. Whisk remaining sauce ingredients in a small bowl. Gradually whisk yogurt mixture into butter, heating just until warmed, 25 seconds (if overcooked, sauce will curdle.)
Assemble by topping each muffin half with a slice of bacon and an egg. Pour some sauce on top and serve extra sauce on the side. Add pepper and parsley to taste.</preparation>
